COUNTER CLAIM ON BEHALF OF RMSCL

IN THE ARBITRAL PROCEEDINGS
RESPONDENT: Rajasthan Medical Services Corporation Ltd. (RMSCL), Jaipur

COUNTER CLAIM STATEMENT

1. COUNTER CLAIM NO. CC-1: Recovery of Cost of Incomplete Work
   Amount: ₹8.75 Crore
   Facts: Contractor abandoned work at 41%. RMSCL had to re-tender the balance work at higher rates.
   Re-tendering differential cost: ₹8.75 Crore.

2. COUNTER CLAIM NO. CC-2: Liquidated Damages (Clause 47 of GCC)
   Amount: ₹4.87 Crore (10% of contract value — maximum LD as per contract)
   Facts: Contractor could not achieve completion within agreed time even with 2 extensions granted.

3. COUNTER CLAIM NO. CC-3: Cost of Supervision During Extended Period
   Amount: ₹84 Lakh
   (Additional supervision cost for 8 months — @ ₹10.5 Lakh/month)

TOTAL COUNTER CLAIM: ₹14.46 Crore

[VERIFY BEFORE FILING: LD applicability disputed — delay was primarily Employer's fault;
per Kath v. State of J&K, LD cannot be levied where delay is attributable to Employer.
Counter-claim CC-2 likely to be rejected by Arbitrator.]
